So I'm working on an Arkanoid clone (with powerups, enemies, etc) as a programming practice project. Using XNA/C# to do it (because I know C# and dot net).<br /><br />What is a good method to detect which side of the block the ball hit (either X or Y) to reflect the balls corresponding velocity (either X or Y).<br /><br />Its a little different than the normal collision detection I'm used to. When it normally doesn't matter where the object was hit.<br /><br />Something like this must be used for Super Mario Bros, as Mario dies if he hits a goomba from the side, but not if it is on the head.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=45">drk421</a> — Wed Aug 25, 2010 5:48 pm</p><hr />
